{
  "texts": [
    "FILCO (Wang et al., 2023c) employs the Wikipedia dataset from the KILT benchmark, referred to as the \"Wizard of Wikipedia\" (WoW), to generate subsequent dialogue.",
    "This process involves basing the output on a Wikipedia article, with the input comprising the history of multiple rounds of dialogue.",
    "RA-DIT (Lin et al., 2023b) also employs the WoW dataset in the fine-tuning phase.",
    "As a result of the command tuning operation, the model outperforms Llama (Touvron et al., 2023a) and Llama-REPLUG (Shi et al., 2023b) with the same parameters for dialogue generation in the zero-shot condition.",
    "The incorporation of Selfmem (Cheng et al., 2024) into the retrieval-augmented generator markedly enhances the generation of dialogue, as a consequence of its remarkable flexibility."
  ]
}